File: platform/browser-extension/src/network-capture.ts

The bug is at lines 397-410. The `getRequests()` function clears `state.requests` (line 407) and `state.requestIdToRequest` (line 408) when `clear=true`, but does not clear `state.pendingRequests` (a Map<string, Partial<CapturedRequest>>). This means in-flight requests that were pending at the time of the clear will still have entries in pendingRequests. When their Network.responseReceived event fires, the handler at line 198 finds the pending entry, creates a completed CapturedRequest, and pushes it to state.requests — but the caller expected a clean slate after the clear.

Fix: Add `state.pendingRequests.clear()` alongside the existing clear logic at line 408:
```typescript
if (clear) {
  state.requests = [];
  state.pendingRequests.clear();
  state.requestIdToRequest.clear();
}
```

Test file: platform/browser-extension/src/network-capture.test.ts — add a test that starts capture, triggers requestWillBeSent (but no responseReceived), calls getRequests(tabId, true), then triggers responseReceived, and verifies the requests array is still empty.
